<br>
Spoilers here, but I'll try not to make them too bad.<br>
<br>
For one thing, the ending.  Now I do think they set themselves up for a problem with the ending in the first place.  It's not like they could just shut off all the machines, there's still all the people in pods, what do they do about that?  But I do think the ending basically sucked.  The focus of the movies somewhere changed from freeing everyone from the machines, to saving Zion and screw everyone else.  <br>
<br>
And let's involve the Merovingian but give him absolutely no real purpose in the story either.  I mean the part he played could have been eliminated entirely without any impact.  He added nothing. <br>
<br>
And I really didn't buy that they'd leave a guy they suspected of killing lots of people completely unguarded and alone with the doctor.  There's suspension of belief for a story, and then there's just stupid.<br>
<br>
And then there was the absolutely pointless death right at the end.  I mean I'm all for offing people, but it had no purpose whatsoever. <br>
<br>
The visuals were great, the big battle at Zion was cool.  Agent Smith was the best part of the whole movie.  <br>
<br>
Overall though, I felt like there was no payoff at all. At least I can hold out hope for Kill Bill volume 2. <p>-Tain<BR>
