Another thing that didn't make much sense was the final fight between Neo and Smith.  Neo's already beaten Smith in the first movie, held his own against hundreds of Smiths in the second movie.  Why exactly should we believe he's going to have trouble with Smith now?  Especially when the rest of them weren't joining in.  There was never a point made of Smith's &quot;power&quot; increasing, just that he was making more and more copies of himself, which is supposedly the intimidating part.  But if the copies are standing around not participating it sort of negates any advantage Smith should have. <br>
<br>
It just doesn't make sense.  <p>-Tain<BR>
